                <p>
                    REPORT VALIDITY PERIOD
                </p>

                <p>

                    Capacity reports are valid for two years if no change is requested by the firm or no change is determined by the Chambers, from the date of issue. Taking into account the warnings made by the chambers, a renewal request should be made a few months before the validity period expires.

                </p>



                <p>
                    If the information in the capacity report changes, it is very important to renew the report in order to avoid problems during bureaucratic procedures.
                </p>



                <p>
                    If the machines in the report are rented (including leasing) and the lease term is less than 2 years, the expiry date of the contract determines the validity period of the report.
                </p>


                <p>
                    If the duration of the Machinery Rental Agreement is less than 1 year on the date of application for the capacity report, a capacity report is not issued for these machines.
                </p>








                <p>
                    <h4>    CAPACITY REPORT RENEWAL-INDUSTRIAL REGISTRATION CERTIFICATE PROCEDURES</h4>
                </p>

                <p>
                    In accordance with the TOBB Law No. 5174 and the Decree of the Council of Ministers dated 16.06.1975 and numbered 7/9914, industrial enterprises located within the working areas of the Chambers are obliged to issue a capacity report and renew their expired capacity reports.
                </p>


                <p>
                    In addition, according to the 41st article of the TOBB Transactions
                    Regulation; In provinces where the Chamber of Industry and the Chamber
                    of Commerce are located separately, companies registered in both Chambers
                    must obtain their capacity reports from the Chambers of Industry.
                </p>


                <p>
                    For this purpose, it is very important to apply to our Chambe
                    r at least one week in advance to renew the validity period
                    of your capacity report, which is important in your industrial
                    and commercial activities, and possible grievances can be prevented.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Our members with a valid Capacity Report can switch to
                    industrial subscription by submitting the Industry
                    Registry Certificate they will receive from the
                    Provincial Directorate of Industry and Trade to
                    TEDAŞ, and they can have the right to use electricity
                    at a rate of 13-27% cheaper than other subscribers.
                </p>


